HEADWORD: Stopped
<hw>Stopped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Phonetics)</fld>
<def>Made by complete closure of the mouth organs; shut; -- said of
certain consonants (<xex>p</xex>, <xex>b</xex>, <xex>t</xex>,
<xex>d</xex>, etc.).</def> <rj><au>H. Sweet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- glottal stop? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stopper</ent>⟦br⟧
